		<p>Ones mood is regulated by several different factors, their environment and their brain chemistry.  It is extremely common for people who are suffering from symptoms of depression, lethargy, and incongruent mood to have deficient inhibitory support, most commonly serotonin.  The only way to tell for sure is through testing.  When serotonin and other neurotransmitters are in balance, we can create a much more receptive environment for change to occur.  When we are able to change the brain, new and positive thinking patterns can occur.</p>
	</section>
	
